description.narrative: In 2019, UNICEF focused interventions in two regions (Maradi and Zinder) accounting for the highest rates of mortality and severe acute malnutrition in children under 5 years of age. UNICEF supported Health System Strengthening and Service Delivery for Reproductive, Maternal, Neonatal Child and Adolescent Health through four packages of high-impact interventions for maternal, newborn, child health, and pediatric HIV/AIDS including in emergency-affected and hard-to-reach areas. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:26/12/2019
